    <!-- Per-language attribute coverage. Every language plugin (Bash, Go, PHP, Python, Rust, Ruby,
         Swift, TS, JS, Dart, etc.) declares its own attribute keys for local variables, parameters,
         functions, properties, etc. Without explicit overrides each one falls back to the parent
         theme (Darcula / Default), which is why teal and steel-blue leak in. The lines below
         inherit from our DEFAULT_* customizations via baseAttributes so every language picks up
         the warm palette automatically. Generated from /tmp/catppuccin-jetbrains/templates/editor.tera
         via /tmp/classify-attrs.py. -->
